title: VELVET BUZZSAW Ending + Monster Explained!
author: Think Story
comment: What did you guys think? Shit or lit?
Coco is the most unlucky character that has to be the one who discovers everyone’s death.

I liked how Josephina says “what’s the point of art if no one sees it” she then becomes a piece of art that no one can see it’s poetic and satisfying

Edit I’ve also noticed how the people who were too shallow to see that they didn’t care about art became it. (Jospehina + Jon)
I don’t see why Morf had to die. Sure, he did bad things, but he had repented when Hobo-man came for him. Unlike the others, who remained clueless.

Never been a student of art but this movie kept my interest. Well acted, great storyline, enjoyed the cinematography. Think Story did a great review and filled in some gaps, helping me gain a deeper understanding.
description:
We break down Netflix's latest horror feature "Velvet Buzzsaw" starring Jake Gyllenhaal and Rene Russo and take a deep dive into explaining some of its greater themes, meaning, and monster!
